-i
--color
--color-match=black on_yellow
--color-lineno=bright_blue
#only search known types
-k 
--pager=more -R
--type-set=ini:ext:ini
--type-set=csv:ext:csv
--type-set=md:ext:markdown,md
#ack uses Perl's Term::ANSIColor module, so you can check what is available to you with:
# > perldoc Term::ANSIColor
#
# The recognized normal foreground color attributes (colors 0 to 7) are:
#
#     black  red  green  yellow  blue  magenta  cyan  white
#
#   The corresponding bright foreground color attributes (colors 8 to 15)
#   are:
#
#     bright_black  bright_red      bright_green  bright_yellow
#     bright_blue   bright_magenta  bright_cyan   bright_white
#
#   The recognized normal background color attributes (colors 0 to 7) are:
#
#     on_black  on_red      on_green  on_yellow
#     on_blue   on_magenta  on_cyan   on_white
#
#   The recognized bright background color attributes (colors 8 to 15) are:
#
#     on_bright_black  on_bright_red      on_bright_green  on_bright_yellow
#     on_bright_blue   on_bright_magenta  on_bright_cyan   on_bright_white
#
#   For any of the above listed attributes, case is not significant.
